        <updateDate>2017-07-25T21:17:19Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Prescription Drug Monitoring Act of </b><b>2017</b></p> <p>This bill requires a state that receives grant funds under the prescription drug monitoring program (PDMP) or the controlled substance monitoring program to comply with specified requirements, including a requirement to share its PDMP data with other states. The Department of Justice (DOJ) or Department of Health and Human Services may withhold grant funds from a state that fails to comply.</p> <p> To facilitate data sharing among states, the bill directs DOJ to award a grant under the Comprehensive Opioid Abuse Grant Program to establish and maintain a data-sharing hub.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
